"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ewh1665702776933.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ewh1665702776933.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ewh1665702776933.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ewh1665702776933\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Informix Stored Procedures\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The INF connector generates stored procedures for the most basic I/O operations in\n      Informix. A stored procedure is one or more SQL statements which have already been parsed and\n      compiled. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50972e1_d50973e1_d50974e1\">Using stored procedures provides better performance than\n         using the equivalent SQL statements. Informix executes stored procedures immediately,\n         because the parsing and compiling has already been done. If you generate or enter SQL\n         statements, Informix first has to parse and compile each one before executing each\n         statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50975e1_d50976e1_d50977e1\">For more information on Informix stored procedures, see your Informix documentation.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__section_pdr_v1f_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d540984e57\">Stored Procedures Created by the INF Connector</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50981e1_d50982e1_d50983e1\">The INF connector creates and uses the stored\n            procedures shown in the table.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Stored procedures created by INF connector</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\">Procedure name </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Explanation </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_E</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Procedure existence check. This procedure checks if table_name has\n                           procedures.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_I</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Insert a row into\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>. This procedure is not created for tables\n                        containing segmented fields. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_F</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Fetch all nonsegmented fields in a row in\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>, for which the row matches a specific\n                        primary key and lock the row if requested. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_U</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Update a row in <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n                        based on either a primary key match or a primary key and U_VERSION field\n                        match. This procedure is not created for tables containing segmented fields.\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_D</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Delete a row in <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n                        based on either a primary key match or a primary key and U_VERSION field\n                        match. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_S</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Select nonsegmented fields for all rows from\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var> using the select cache. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_S</code>\n</p>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">#</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ewh1665702776933__table_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1__entry__2\">Select nonsegmented fields for rows from\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">table_name</var> using index number <var class=\"keyword varname\">#</var>;\n                        use select cache. The connector generates a stored procedure for each index\n                        referred to in such select operations. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__note_gv1_y1f_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Additional stored procedures can be generated to\n            enforce referential integrity.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50987e1_d50988e1_d50989e1\">The connector creates stored procedures when it\n            creates the associated base table, granting execute permissions to public on the stored\n            procedures.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50990e1_d50991e1_d50992e1\">Uniface can only create and execute stored procedures\n            if you set the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lbw1665702728801.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lbw1665702728801.html\" title=\"Enable stored procedures.\">procs</a> connector option in the assignment\n            file.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__section_ztp_y1f_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d540984e251\">Segmented Fields </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d50996e1_d50997e1_d50998e1\">The connector never uses stored procedures to\n            manipulate segmented fields and the connector does not create <code class=\"ph codeph\">insert</code> or\n            update <code class=\"ph codeph\">stored</code> procedures for tables containing segmented fields. The\n            connector creates the other stored procedures, but these do not retrieve or modify\n            segmented fields. The connector uses dynamic SQL to execute the relevant Read, Write,\n            and Update requests.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__section_sr3_gbf_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d540984e266\">Serial Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ewh1665702776933__p_d51002e1_d51003e1_d51004e1\">If the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqj1665702728942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqj1665702728942.html\" title=\"Insert specific values into serial fields.\">serial insert</a> connector\n            option is set on together with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">procs</code> connector option, the\n            connector does not use the ‘insert’ stored procedure for tables that contain Serial\n            fields. Instead, dynamic SQL is used to execute the relevant Write request.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Informix Stored Procedures Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Informix Stored Procedures The INF connector generates stored procedures for the most basic I/O operations in Informix. A stored procedure is one or more SQL statements which have already been parsed and compiled. Using stored procedures provides better performance than using the equivalent SQL statements. Informix executes stored procedures immediately, because the parsing and compiling has already been done. If you generate or enter SQL statements, Informix first has to parse and compile each one before executing each statement. For more information on Informix stored procedures, see your Informix documentation. Stored Procedures Created by the INF Connector The INF connector creates and uses the stored procedures shown in the table. Table 1. Stored procedures created by INF connector Procedure name Explanation table_name _E Procedure existence check. This procedure checks if table_name has procedures. table_name _I Insert a row into table_name . This procedure is not created for tables containing segmented fields. table_name _F Fetch all nonsegmented fields in a row in table_name , for which the row matches a specific primary key and lock the row if requested. table_name _U Update a row in table_name based on either a primary key match or a primary key and U_VERSION field match. This procedure is not created for tables containing segmented fields. table_name _D Delete a row in table_name based on either a primary key match or a primary key and U_VERSION field match. table_name _S Select nonsegmented fields for all rows from table_name using the select cache. table_name _S # Select nonsegmented fields for rows from table_name using index number # ; use select cache. The connector generates a stored procedure for each index referred to in such select operations. Note: Additional stored procedures can be generated to enforce referential integrity. The connector creates stored procedures when it creates the associated base table, granting execute permissions to public on the stored procedures. Uniface can only create and execute stored procedures if you set the procs connector option in the assignment file. Segmented Fields The connector never uses stored procedures to manipulate segmented fields and the connector does not create insert or update stored procedures for tables containing segmented fields. The connector creates the other stored procedures, but these do not retrieve or modify segmented fields. The connector uses dynamic SQL to execute the relevant Read, Write, and Update requests. Serial Fields If the serial insert connector option is set on together with the procs connector option, the connector does not use the ‘insert’ stored procedure for tables that contain Serial fields. Instead, dynamic SQL is used to execute the relevant Write request. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}